         <abstract>
            <p>We present spectral methods for solving the Stokes problem in a circular domain. Their main feature is the uniform inf-sup condition, which allows for optimal error estimates. We apply them to the resolution of exterior problems by coupling with the transparent boundary condition.</p>
          </abstract>
